You can test the endpoint using curl by sending an image of a food label:

Bash
curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/scan-food" \
     -H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
     -F "file=C:\Users\syeds\PycharmProjects\NutriScanAI\samples\label-1.jpg"

Sample Response
JSON
{
  "status": "Red",
  "reason": "Your current blood sugar is 145 mg/dL. This item contains 35g of added sugar, which will likely cause a dangerous glucose spike.",
  "nutrients_detected": {
    "sugar": "35g",
    "sodium": "210mg"
  }
}